---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About - Joel Stransky">
  <main class="w-full bg-surface-primary text-foreground-primary transition-colors duration-300">
    <div class="mx-auto px-6 md:px-24 max-w-3xl py-16 md:py-24">
      <h1 class="font-serif font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl text-foreground-primary tracking-tight mb-12">
        About Joel Stransky
      </h1>
      
      <div class="font-sans text-base md:text-lg text-foreground-secondary leading-relaxed space-y-8">
        <p>
          I am a Senior Software Engineer, UI/UX Designer, and Game Artist with over 30 years of experience developing interactive web applications. My work focuses on bridging the gap between interface design and front-end engineering architecture. I manage complex application state, design tokens, and browser-level runtime optimizations across various tech stacks, specializing in TypeScript, React, Next.js, SCSS, and monorepos.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          My background includes engineering tools, framework standards, and custom browser extension components. At Konami Gaming, I replaced a legacy interface by implementing an open-source Chromium integration framework within a Java runtime, eliminating corporate software licensing fees and enabling native extension support for debugging. At College Loan Corporation, I consolidated six disparate platforms into a unified design system using variables and components in Figma, while optimizing layout performance to move site Google Lighthouse scores from C to A ratings.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          I have also developed reusable parent-theme architectures for the University of Hawaii and contributed to the ePib framework standard for the Barnes & Noble Nook Color rollout. My graphics and 3D engineering experience spans Game Art training at Full Sail University to building real-time client-server physics orchestration using TypeScript and React within Roblox. My current focus includes implementing Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers and structuring developer automation tools.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
